From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 15:30:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] rockchip: rk3576-generic: enable USB host, storage, and
 keyboard

Add the USB host stack so the box can be driven with a USB keyboard and
boot or flash from a USB mass-storage stick with no laptop and no serial
console. USB_XHCI_HCD is the load-bearing symbol: the dwc3-generic host
driver calls xhci_register(), so without an XHCI HCD there is no host,
and it selects USB_HOST for us. USB_KEYBOARD (+ DM_KEYBOARD) and
CONSOLE_MUX let the keyboard join serial as console input.

The host runs on drd1 (patch "run USB host on the second controller").
drd0 stays a peripheral: rk3576-generic.dts sets it to "peripheral", so
it remains the rockusb/ums gadget port -- a `reboot loader` from Linux
comes back up in rockusb, and the `ums` command exports a block device
to a laptop. u-boot has no runtime OTG role switch on these nodes, so a
single controller cannot be both a host and a gadget; keeping drd0 the
device port and running host on drd1 gives both roles at once, one per
connector.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig b/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
index 501b1951..94f6a84a 100644
--- a/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
+++ b/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
@@ -21,6 +21,7 @@ CONFIG_CMD_GPT=y
 CONFIG_CMD_MISC=y
 CONFIG_CMD_MMC=y
 CONFIG_CMD_ROCKUSB=y
+CONFIG_CMD_USB=y
 CONFIG_CMD_USB_MASS_STORAGE=y
 # CONFIG_CMD_SETEXPR is not set
 CONFIG_CMD_RNG=y
@@ -45,9 +46,15 @@ CONFIG_DEBUG_UART_SHIFT=2
 CONFIG_SYS_NS16550_MEM32=y
 CONFIG_SYSRESET_PSCI=y
 CONFIG_USB=y
+CONFIG_USB_XHCI_HCD=y
+CONFIG_USB_XHCI_DWC3=y
 CONFIG_USB_DWC3=y
 CONFIG_USB_DWC3_GENERIC=y
 CONFIG_USB_GADGET=y
 CONFIG_USB_GADGET_DOWNLOAD=y
 CONFIG_USB_FUNCTION_ROCKUSB=y
+CONFIG_USB_STORAGE=y
+CONFIG_USB_KEYBOARD=y
+CONFIG_DM_KEYBOARD=y
+CONFIG_CONSOLE_MUX=y
 CONFIG_ERRNO_STR=y
